          <li><a href="about.html">About the student and the purpose of the project</a></li>
        </ol>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section timeline-strip">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <h2>HTTP at a glance</h2>
        <p>New versions kept the same core goal while improving speed and efficiency.</p>
      </div>
      <ol class="timeline-list">
        <li><strong>HTTP/0.9</strong><span>Simple document retrieval with only the <code>GET</code> method.</span></li>
        <li><strong>HTTP/1.0</strong><span>Added headers and status codes so responses could explain what happened.</span></li>
        <li><strong>HTTP/1.1</strong><span>Added persistent connections and better caching support.</span></li>
        <li><strong>HTTP/2</strong><span>Added multiplexing and binary framing for better performance.</span></li>
        <li><strong>HTTP/3</strong><span>Uses QUIC to cut latency and improve behavior on unstable networks.</span></li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="page-section table-wrap">
      <table>
        <caption>Website page overview</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Page</th>
            <th>Purpose</th>
